'''Irish twins''' is a [[slang]] term that refers to siblings born 9 to 12 months apart - usually in the same calendar year, or who are in the same grade in school. The term is considered both endearing and misguided, because it references a perception about families of [[Irish Catholic]]s who do not use birth control (and thus may have children in quick succession), but it is often used endearingly by the families of the "twins" themselves. 

Similarly, '''[[Irish triplets]]''' means three children in three years.

